                content: `**Environmental Management Agency (EMA)**
- **EMA** (Environmental Management Agency) is Zimbabwe’s **national** body for **environmental** **regulation** and **protection**. It works on **pollution** control (air, water, land), **waste** management, **environmental** **impact** **assessments** (EIAs) for **development** projects, **awareness** and **education**, and **enforcement** of **environmental** laws.

**Ministry of Environment, Climate and Wildlife**
- The **Ministry** sets **policy** and **coordinates** **environmental** and **climate** action. It aligns with **Zimbabwe** **Vision** **2030** (national development goals) and with **international** commitments such as the **UN Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs)** — especially **SDG 11** (sustainable cities), **SDG 12** (responsible consumption and production), **SDG 13** (climate action), **SDG 14** (life below water), **SDG 15** (life on land).

**Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs)**
- The **SDGs** are **global** targets agreed by the **UN** for **2030** — including **ending** **poverty**, **protecting** the **planet**, and **ensuring** **peace** and **prosperity**. **Environmental** goals include **climate** action, **clean** water and **sanitation**, **affordable** clean **energy**, **sustainable** use of **ecosystems** (forests, oceans, land). **Environmental management** in Zimbabwe (and globally) is **linked** to these **goals** — e.g. **reducing** **deforestation**, **protecting** **biodiversity**, **reducing** **pollution**, **promoting** **sustainable** **development**.`,
