                content: `**Main commercial crops (Zimbabwe)**
- **Tobacco** — **Flue-cured** tobacco; **main** **foreign** **exchange** earner; **NR II**; **irrigation** or **rainfed**; **labour** and **capital** intensive; **tobacco** curing uses **wood** (deforestation concern).
- **Maize** — **Staple** food and **fodder**; **NR II** and **III**; **rainfed** or **irrigated**; **communal** and **commercial**.
- **Cotton** — **NR II** and **III**; **rainfed**; **smallholder** and **commercial**; **export** and **local** textile industry.
- **Wheat, barley** — **Winter** crops; **irrigation** in **NR II**; **commercial**.
- **Sugar cane** — **Irrigation** in **lowveld** (e.g. Triangle, Hippo Valley); **estates** and **outgrowers**; **sugar** and **ethanol**.
- **Tea, coffee** — **NR I** (Eastern Highlands); **plantation** or **estate**.
- **Horticulture** — **Vegetables**, **fruit** (citrus, deciduous), **flowers**; **irrigation**; **export** and **local**.
- **Soya beans, groundnuts, paprika** — **NR II**; **oil**, **spice**, **food**.

**Communal vs commercial**
- **Communal** areas — **Subsistence** and **small-scale** **commercial**; **maize**, **millet**, **groundnuts**, **livestock**; **limited** **capital** and **inputs**; **vulnerable** to **drought**. **Commercial** (before and after land reform) — **Large** or **medium** scale; **tobacco**, **maize**, **cotton**, **wheat**; **higher** inputs; **markets** and **export**. **Land reform** (see below) **redistributed** much **commercial** land to **resettled** farmers; **production** and **structure** **changed** significantly.`,
                diagrams: [],
